  "doc_id": "1512",
  "text": "Macrophages express the highest amount of Ragulator components (Lamtor1, 2, 3, 4 and 5) and v-ATPase components, compared with other types of cells and tissues (accecible online at BioGPS [CITATION_1] ) . We focused on Lamtor1, which anchors the other four Lamtor proteins on lysosome membranes [CITATION_2] . To investigate the role of Lamtor1 in macrophages, we established conditional knockout (KO) mice lacking Lamtor1 in macrophages (Lamtor1 flox/flox LysM-Cre). To test the system, we generated bone marrow À derived macrophages (BMDMs), and confirmed the complete deletion of Lamtor1 in these cells ( Supplementary  Fig. 1a-c) . In Lamtor1 À deficient BMDMs, amounts of other Ragulator components, namely Lamtor2 À 5, were also reduced ( Supplementary Fig. 1c ). Subcellular localization of Lamtor1 was the lysosome/late endosome ( Supplementary Fig. 1d ), as previously reported in HEK293T cells [CITATION_3] and mouse fibroblasts [CITATION_4] . The development of immune system was not affected in 6 À 8-week-old conditional KO mice. The numbers of monocyte/macrophages, neutrophils, T cells and B cells in the bone marrow and the spleen, and the development of T cells in the thymus, were comparable between conditional KO mice and littermate controls (Lamtor1 flox/flox ) ( Supplementary Fig. 2 ).",
